    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix copy-paste error in F1AP CU Configuration Update Acknowledge decoder\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_f1ap_cu_configuration_update_acknowledge` function was missing handling for several ProtocolIEs that can be present in the message. This caused the function to fail with \"unknown protocol IE\" errors when processing valid F1AP messages containing these IEs.\n\nThe issue was introduced when this function was created by copying from a similar function but not updating all the protocol IE handling cases for its new context.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_interface_management.c`: Added missing switch cases for:\n  - `F1AP_ProtocolIE_ID_id_CriticalityDiagnostics`\n  - `F1AP_ProtocolIE_ID_id_Dedicated_SIDelivery_NeededUE_List` \n  - GNB-CU TNL Association Setup List (ID 132)\n  - GNB-CU TNL Association Failed To Setup List (ID 134)\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing F1AP CU Configuration Update Acknowledge messages that contain Criticality Diagnostics or TNL Association lists, the decoder would hit the default case and fail with:\n```\nAssertError: F1AP_ProtocolIE_ID_id 132 unknown\n```\n\nThis prevented proper handling of configuration update acknowledgements in F1AP interface management procedures.\n"
}